{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PeUdJTEgYnyTdKeeerFuqR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a known MongoDB restriction: when you add an arbiter to a 2-member PSS (Primary-Secondary-Secondary) or 2-member PS replica set, it can change the implicit default write concern. MongoDB 5.0+ introduced stricter rules around this.\n\nThe current set has 2 data-bearing members. With majority write concern (the default), writes need acknowledgment from 2 members (majority of 2 = 2, so both must ack). If we add an arbiter, the total votes become 3, majority becomes 2, but writableMembersCount stays 2. So the implicit default write concern would stay at {w: majority} meaning 2 writable members.\nActually, I need to reconsider how MongoDB calculates the implicit default write concern. It's based on whether there are enough non-arbiter members capable of becoming primary and whether the number of data-bearing voting members exceeds 1—if both conditions are met, the IDWC becomes {w: \"majority\"}, otherwise it's {w: 1}. With the current 2 data-bearing voting members, I need to verify which rule applies. The majority calculation stays at 2 writes whether it's 2 data-bearing members or 3 total voters (2 data-bearing + 1 arbiter), but the issue is that the current config explicitly sets IDWC to {w: 2} tied to both members, and adding the arbiter would change what the implicit default becomes. MongoDB recommends explicitly setting the default write concern before reconfiguring...\n\nWriting config command...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":208,"cache_read_input_tokens":32707,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":208},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b523417-e9f0-4a93-988e-3d7062b3ce78","uuid":"a6e6ec59-9bab-43e9-97a6-9d9cf7b84404","request_id":"req_011CccLvGdshcdzatX2B6eKg"}
