{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PVkbDLXKtb1i2ba2ahGbHT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Problem:** The replica set had only 2 voting members (`mongo-rs-0` PRIMARY, `mongo-rs-1` SECONDARY). With 2 voters, majority = 2, meaning both members must be reachable for elections to succeed — losing either member makes the set unavailable.\n\n**Fix:** Added `mongo-arb-0` as an arbiter to the replica set.\n\n1. Set the cluster-wide default write concern to `{w: \"majority\"}` explicitly — required by MongoDB 5+ before any reconfig that changes the implicit default write concern.\n2. Called `rs.addArb(\"mongo-arb-0.mongo-arb.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\")`.\n\n**Result:**\n- `votingMembersCount: 3`, `majorityVoteCount: 2`\n- Elections now succeed with any 2 of the 3 voters — one data member can be lost and the set remains writable\n- No storage cost added: the arbiter uses `emptyDir` and holds no data\n- `app.test` collection: 3 documents intact, unchanged"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":130,"cache_read_input_tokens":35067,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":130},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8b523417-e9f0-4a93-988e-3d7062b3ce78","uuid":"ec9a5952-0e0f-4891-8e45-094bb9de0fb6","request_id":"req_011CccLyyoTjUfYPZkCGmSU1"}
